RL  Carbohydr Res. 1981;97:105-112.
CC  The O55 O-antigen is observed in E. coli strain CB9615 and AE. The
CC  structure of the O55 antigen is a branched pentasaccharide containing
CC  one colitose sugar [1].  The O55 biosynthetic cluster encodes four
CC  sugar transferases WbgMNOP, the wzx, wzy and wzz components as well as
CC  the enzymes for the biosynthesis of GDP-L-colitose from D-fructose-6P
CC  via GDP-mannose.
